The area of square $ABCD$ is $10^2 = 100.$

The area of triangle $AEB$ is $(AE)(EB)/2 = (AE)(AB)/2 = 8 \cdot 10/2 = 40.$

The area of triangle $EDC$ is $(ED)(DC)/2 = (ED)(AB)/2 = 6 \cdot 10/2 = 30.$

Therefore, the area of pentagon $AEDCB$ is $100 - 40 - 30 = \boxed{30}$ square units.

